02:45.617 --> 02:47.134
(school bell ringing)

02:50.155 --> 02:54.108
So, are you jumping
on this superhero bandwagon?

02:54.142 --> 02:57.361
A club where you have
to wear full-body spandex?

02:57.412 --> 02:58.946
Not really my thing.

02:58.980 --> 03:00.147
Good, that means you'll be free

03:00.165 --> 03:03.450
to hang out Friday night...
you and me.

03:03.484 --> 03:04.651
What do you say?

03:04.669 --> 03:06.754
Um... I...

03:06.788 --> 03:07.755
RYDER:
Marley's got

03:07.789 --> 03:09.089
plans on Friday, dude.

03:09.124 --> 03:11.324
The football team's
got an away game

03:11.343 --> 03:13.127
at Lawrence, and I asked her
if she'd come cheer us on.

03:13.161 --> 03:14.628
See, Jake, it's funny.

03:14.662 --> 03:16.096
Girls don't like it
when you make it seem

03:16.131 --> 03:17.598
like you're really into them

03:17.632 --> 03:18.632
and then totally blow them off.

03:18.666 --> 03:21.334
You know what, dude?

03:21.353 --> 03:23.170
I don't remember asking
for your opinion.

03:23.188 --> 03:24.838
Guys, don't do this.
Whoa.

03:24.856 --> 03:26.106
Whoa, you're
really intimidating.

03:26.141 --> 03:27.441
Let me ask you
a question... what kind

03:27.475 --> 03:28.842
of a name is Ryder Lynn
anyway? 'Cause it sounds

03:28.860 --> 03:30.010
like your parents named you
after a cowgirl doll

03:30.028 --> 03:32.345
who comes with her own pony.

03:32.364 --> 03:34.314
Look, man, I don't
want any trouble.

03:34.348 --> 03:36.150
I know you're a badass.
You want to know how I know

03:36.184 --> 03:38.351
you're such a badass? Because
you ride a Razor scooter.

03:38.370 --> 03:41.688
Nothing says "I'm a badass"
like a Razor scooter.

03:41.706 --> 03:43.624
Guys, please, don't do this.

03:43.658 --> 03:46.026
It... this is...
this is stupid. Stop.

03:46.044 --> 03:47.828
Hey, hey, cut it out.

03:47.862 --> 03:49.196
Stop. Come on, stop, stop it.

03:49.214 --> 03:50.530
Stop. Cut it out.
Come on.

03:50.548 --> 03:53.133
I persuade you
to stop fighting immediately.

03:53.168 --> 03:54.534
Freeze, bitches.

03:54.552 --> 03:55.535
FINN:
Thanks, Becky,

03:55.553 --> 03:57.537
both you guys.

03:57.555 --> 03:59.372
Glee Club, 20 minutes.

03:59.391 --> 04:01.374
(school bell ringing)

04:01.393 --> 04:03.394
(indistinct chatter)

04:06.881 --> 04:08.849
(laughter)

04:08.883 --> 04:11.384
Okay, guys, sit down. We got
a lot of work to do today.

04:11.403 --> 04:12.686
(indistinct chatter)

04:12.720 --> 04:14.405
No, seriously, come on,
I mean it, sit down.

04:15.740 --> 04:18.725
Okay, so the first
order of business today

04:18.743 --> 04:20.661
is to welcome the newest members
to the glee club...

04:20.695 --> 04:23.163
Ryder and Kitty.
(cheering and applause)

04:23.198 --> 04:25.532
Wait, don't we all get
to vote on her or something?

04:25.566 --> 04:28.068
Well, Tina,
Kitty was fantastic in <i>Grease.</i>

04:28.086 --> 04:29.569
In spite of my god-awful part.

04:29.587 --> 04:31.171
Besides, we're under the gun.

04:31.206 --> 04:32.673
We... we have to go
to Sectionals next week

04:32.707 --> 04:34.541
and we need 12 members
to compete.

04:34.575 --> 04:35.909
Oh, well, then,
just call Santana back

04:35.927 --> 04:37.845
from Kentucky again
'cause apparently she's better

04:37.879 --> 04:39.179
than anyone who's actually
enrolled here.

04:39.214 --> 04:40.413
Look, Tina, not now.

04:40.432 --> 04:41.748
Uh, look, where was I?

04:41.766 --> 04:43.583
Sectionals, yes.

04:43.601 --> 04:45.102
Here's the game plan.

04:47.088 --> 04:49.089
Broke the marker.

04:50.225 --> 04:51.775
Where does Mr. Shue keep
the other markers?

04:52.927 --> 04:54.695
Uh...

04:57.431 --> 04:58.899
Screw it. Uh...

05:01.953 --> 05:04.371
The theme is "Foreigner."

05:04.405 --> 05:08.041
We're gonna sing songs by
Foreigner in foreign languages,

05:08.076 --> 05:10.711
wearing all the costumes
of the world's nations.

05:14.132 --> 05:15.582
Wait, seriously,
that's your idea?

05:15.616 --> 05:16.583
Yeah.

05:16.617 --> 05:18.418
Kiki, what do you think?

05:18.452 --> 05:20.254
FEMALE VOICE: I think I'm
alive and you're the machine.

05:20.288 --> 05:22.455
BLAINE:
Finn, times have changed.

05:22.474 --> 05:24.057
We're national champions
now, which means

05:24.092 --> 05:26.393
we have to exceed all
expectations, so if that's

05:26.427 --> 05:30.964
your best idea, I... I don't
think we stand a chance.

05:30.982 --> 05:32.799
Wait, where are you going?

05:32.817 --> 05:36.303
I'm going to get our trophy back
from the Warblers...

05:36.321 --> 05:38.638
the one you haven't even noticed
is missing.

05:40.992 --> 05:42.442
Crap, uh...

05:42.476 --> 05:45.412
<i>So, who exactly</i>
<i>are you supposed to be?</i>

05:45.446 --> 05:47.447
I'm the Beiste Master.

05:47.481 --> 05:48.481
Blaine said

05:48.500 --> 05:49.983
I couldn't be faculty advisor

05:50.001 --> 05:51.318
unless I dressed up once a week,

05:51.336 --> 05:53.486
so I'm from
the planet Testostergen,

05:53.505 --> 05:54.755
I can digest any
known substance

05:54.789 --> 05:57.124
and cry at the drop of a hat,

05:57.158 --> 05:58.792
and, hey, I'm not kidding
about that last part.

05:58.826 --> 06:01.428
Last night I teared up
at an Activia commercial.

06:01.462 --> 06:02.429
(chuckles)

06:02.463 --> 06:03.997
This is just all so ridiculous.

06:04.015 --> 06:06.266
Oh, come on, pumpkin,
this is fun.

06:06.301 --> 06:07.634
Yeah, it's no wonder
superheroes

06:07.668 --> 06:08.969
are all the rage.

06:09.003 --> 06:10.888
Putting on a mask
is like getting up onstage.

06:10.939 --> 06:12.339
It gives you the freedom to be

06:12.357 --> 06:14.674
the person
you secretly aspire to be,

06:14.692 --> 06:17.978
and if you ask me, the world
could use a few more heroes.

06:18.012 --> 06:19.530
(school bell ringing)
So, what's bugging you, kiddo?

06:19.564 --> 06:20.697
You seem blue.

06:20.732 --> 06:22.349
It was my first lesson
in Glee Club today,

06:22.367 --> 06:23.617
and it was a total disaster.

06:23.651 --> 06:25.852
What happened?
I don't know.

06:25.870 --> 06:27.020
I mean, the lesson
that I planned

06:27.038 --> 06:28.021
was awesome.

06:28.039 --> 06:29.323
I... I think
it's just that the...

06:29.357 --> 06:31.358
the glee club doesn't see me
as an adult.

06:31.376 --> 06:33.994
(groans)

06:34.028 --> 06:35.462
God, is that
what coffee tastes like?

06:35.496 --> 06:36.863
How do people drink that?

06:36.881 --> 06:38.081
I'm just spitballing here,

06:38.132 --> 06:40.033
but maybe you should invest
in a pair of tights.

06:40.051 --> 06:42.002
You know, Clark Kent
was an awesome guy,

06:42.036 --> 06:45.372
but it was Superman
who inspired everyone.

06:45.390 --> 06:47.474
Be their hero, Finn.

06:47.508 --> 06:49.509
I'm just saying.

06:51.896 --> 06:54.698
(bell clanging)

06:56.717 --> 06:58.819
Sebastian.

06:58.853 --> 07:00.220
Of course it was you.

07:00.238 --> 07:02.689
No, it wasn't, I swear.

07:02.723 --> 07:04.942
I turned over a new leaf,
remember?

07:04.993 --> 07:08.028
No more bullying, blackmail
or assault this year.

07:08.062 --> 07:09.830
That must be boring for you.

07:09.864 --> 07:13.083
Yeah, it is;
Being nice sucks.

07:14.402 --> 07:16.569
He's waiting for you
in the library.

07:16.588 --> 07:18.071
Who is?

07:18.089 --> 07:20.374
The guy you're here to see.

07:20.408 --> 07:21.574
Captain of the Warblers.

07:21.593 --> 07:24.678
I thought you were captain
of the Warblers.

07:33.104 --> 07:35.088
I knew they'd send you.

07:35.106 --> 07:38.091
Allow me to answer
the obvious questions.

07:38.109 --> 07:41.862
I'm Hunter Clarington, I am
the new captain of the Warblers,

07:41.896 --> 07:43.697
and I'm not even
remotely bi-curious.

07:43.731 --> 07:45.065
How are you captain
of the Warblers when...?

07:45.099 --> 07:46.933
When you've never
seen me before?

07:46.951 --> 07:49.486
Simple.

07:49.537 --> 07:51.204
Dalton just gave me
a full scholarship

07:51.239 --> 07:53.106
to move here
from Colorado Springs,

07:53.124 --> 07:55.192
where I led
my military academy choir

07:55.226 --> 07:56.776
to a Regionals victory

07:56.794 --> 07:58.996
with presidential honors.

07:59.047 --> 08:01.882
Now I'm here to kick it up a
notch, and that starts with you.

08:01.916 --> 08:03.083
That's very intimidating.

08:03.117 --> 08:04.451
Where's the trophy, Hunter?

08:04.485 --> 08:06.336
(chuckles)

08:06.387 --> 08:07.971
Don't worry, it's safe.

08:10.591 --> 08:12.059
It was just bait after all.

08:12.093 --> 08:13.560
See, you're kind of

08:13.594 --> 08:14.728
a legend here.

08:14.762 --> 08:15.896
I like that.

08:15.930 --> 08:17.230
So here's my offer:

08:17.265 --> 08:18.682
Your little diversity club

08:18.733 --> 08:20.934
can have its
Nationals trophy back

08:20.968 --> 08:22.402
when you rejoin the Warblers.

08:22.437 --> 08:25.272
And why would
I ever leave McKinley?

08:25.306 --> 08:26.406
Why would you stay?

08:26.441 --> 08:28.275
I heard you only went there
to be with Kurt,

08:28.309 --> 08:29.409
right?

08:29.444 --> 08:30.444
In fact,

08:30.478 --> 08:34.948
I hear they even call you
Blaine Warbler.

08:34.982 --> 08:36.950
They know you don't
belong there,

08:36.984 --> 08:38.802
so why don't you?
