I don't know why this
stuff is so hard for me.

25:55.221 --> 25:57.222
Am I stupid?
No.

25:57.256 --> 25:58.707
You're actually very smart.

25:58.725 --> 26:01.593
(school bell ringing)

26:06.099 --> 26:08.717
It's not a brain tumor, is it?
No.

26:10.069 --> 26:12.104
Uh, I'm dyslexic.

26:13.272 --> 26:16.391
You know, do you
know what it's like

26:16.409 --> 26:18.226
to have a real secret identity?

26:18.244 --> 26:21.246
Not like Clark Kent
or Peter Parker,

26:21.280 --> 26:24.916
but to know inside you're not
who everyone thinks you are.

26:26.619 --> 26:30.905
My whole life, it's been, "Ryder
just needs to apply himself."

26:30.923 --> 26:32.708
"Ryder's smart; he just
needs to work harder,

26:32.742 --> 26:35.744
focus, get it
together, man up."

26:39.298 --> 26:41.600
But inside, man, I knew
they were all wrong.

26:41.634 --> 26:43.935
It didn't matter
how hard I focused

26:43.970 --> 26:46.104
